Title: Building A Baby  
Author: Paul R. Cohen, Tim Oates, Marc S. Atkin Carole R. Beal 
Address: Amherst, MA 01003  
Affiliation: Department of Computer Science  Department of Psychology University of Massachusetts,  
Abstract: We show how an agent can acquire conceptual knowledge by sensorimotor interaction with its environment. The method has much in common with the notion of image-schemas, which are central to Mandler's theory of conceptual development. We show that Mandler's approach is feasible in an artificial agent. 
